rComments: Myong is very passionate about research and it shows in the class. If you understand the papers inside and out, you'll be fine on the tests.
Myong's class was very interesting and a great intro to BIOE classes.

If you have experience reading scientific papers, you're fine. Otherwise, this class is very difficult and she's very unclear in her explanations and it's hard to remain attentive during class. I will never take another class with her. Smart lady though. Nice too.
Unhelpful, Uninterested professor. Can't explain topics at all. Difficult exams. No office hours. The classes topics and articles were very interesting but the professor lacked all teaching ability.

Well-taught class with lots of great features: weekly journal discussions, almost no homework, and a fun group project. Prof Myong really encourages students to put serious work into the projects, and students get a lot out of it. Super approachable, friendly person.
